<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF206A9FFD259E5F1CAEB26E" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF206A9FFD259E5F1CAEB26E" blockId="219.[728,1322,1931,2359]" lastBlockId="219.[108,1320,2363,3227]" pageId="219" pageNumber="981">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFC869E5F1DCEB311" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[890,974,2054,2083]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFC139E5F1A3CB311" authorityName="Borkhausen" authorityYear="1797" box="[1007,1084,2054,2083]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="myotis">myotis</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFD259E701DB0B378" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[729,944,2089,2122]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bombinus">Myotis bombinus</taxonomicName>
is often included as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFC879E081A1CB340" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[891,1052,2129,2162]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nattereri">M. nattereri</taxonomicName>
, but genetic data place it closer to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFC359E211A75B3AB" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1908" box="[969,1141,2168,2201]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="980" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pequinius">M. pequinius</taxonomicName>
and possibly 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFD259EFD1D6EB3F3" authorityName="Kormos" authorityYear="1934" box="[729,878,2212,2241]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="979" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="schaubi">M. schaubi</taxonomicName>
, M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFC459EFD1A2CB3F3" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[953,1068,2212,2241]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chinensis">chinensis</taxonomicName>
, and M. escalarai than to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFCB99E9E1DDBB3DA" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[837,987,2247,2280]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nattereri">M. nattereri</taxonomicName>
, although some genetic studies found differing relationships. It has been suggested the amurensis is a distinct species. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF206A9FFF8E9F3A1AC6B2C9" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" type="synonymic_list">
